<br>
Whoever has all the stadium money has zero obligation to humanity.  They are attempting to turn a profit on that money that will indefinitely meet the needs of their family, their employees' families.  Money is a privilege, and charity should be reserved for the truly helpless needy (veterans, abandonded children come to mind).  What sense does it make to work your ass off, and give it away to largely useless fucks that could be working?<br>
<br>
Aalandan if anything is too compassionate.  I choose to give money to United Way every year via my employer, but how much money do I fork out where I have no choice?  Until we get a libertarian in office, and everyone eats, sleeps, lives and dies on their own merits, nobody will have to accept responsibility for their own fate.<br>
